Primary Column-6 OLS of weekly RV^(1/3) on the AR(1)-filtered remittance surprise plus six controls, estimated on the Colombian weekly panel from {{ primary.date_min }} to {{ primary.date_max }}. The two-sided T3b gate rule `|β̂_Rem / SE(β̂_Rem)| > 1.645` at α = 0.10 is the pre-committed primary; the above headline is a single deterministic summary of that test outcome. Three-way verdict enum: PASS / FAIL / INCONCLUSIVE (the latter separates underpowered null from mechanism absence via the 0.20-SD MDES rule, spec §4.5).

## Anti-fishing framing

This exercise tests a distinct macro mechanism (external-inflow channel) from the prior CPI-surprise Rev-4 exercise (inflation channel). It is **NOT a rescue** of the CPI-FAIL verdict (2026-04-19). Provenance: `REMITTANCE_VOLATILITY_SWAP.md` mtime 2026-04-02 predates the CPI-FAIL by 17 days, establishing the remittance channel as a pre-existing candidate mechanism (Rev-1 spec §10; design doc §"Why this is not a rescue of CPI-FAIL").

