## Forest Plot

![NB3 §8 sensitivity forest plot — primary anchor + 13 pre-registered sensitivity rows](figures/forest_plot.png)

Fourteen specifications are plotted with 90% HAC CI whiskers: the primary Column-6 anchor at the top (divider below), then the 13 pre-registered sensitivity rows S1–S13 (A1-R monthly, A4 release-day-excluded, release-day-only, pre/post-2015, Dec-Jan-excluded, SARIMA-seasonal, current-vintage, quarterly corridor reconstruction, alternate log(RV) LHS, GARCH-X variance-equation, Petro-Trump event-dummied, event-study co-primary).

**Pre-registered anti-fishing protocol** (Rev-1 spec §6): under a PASS gate, material-mover §9 spotlight in NB3 is emitted; under FAIL or INCONCLUSIVE, §9 cells emit placeholders referencing the sensitivity-row pre-registration and assert that no post-hoc spotlight is performed. This prevents specification-search bias (Simonsohn, Simmons & Nelson 2020; Ankel-Peters, Brodeur & Connolly 2024) — the FAIL verdict is an informative scientific output, not a trigger for further rescue attempts.

